  "A retail company has $5 million in inventory, $3 million in accounts receivable, and $2 million in accounts payable. Its net working capital is:": "",
  "$3 million": "",
  "$6 million": "",
  "$8 million": "",
  "$10 million": "",
  "Net working capital = Current Assets - Current Liabilities = ($5M inventory + $3M receivables) - $2M payables = $8M - $2M = $6M. This represents the capital tied up in day-to-day operations that must be funded.": ""
